The paper deals with the problem of compressing a source sequence in the presence of side-information, which is related to the source via insertions, deletions, and substitutions. This problem is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS) since the algorithm proposed in the paper encodes the edits contained in runs of different extents separately. The paper also discusses the compression rate of the algorithm, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with side-information, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SP) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
